B.a8m=new A.dt("Welcome!","This app teaches you how to build **finite automata**, **pushdown automata**, and **Turing machines** \u2014 the fundamental models of computation.\n\nEach level asks you to build an automaton that matches a target language. Follow these tutorials first to learn the tools, then dive in!",B.c_)
B.a88=new A.hz(1,"addNode")
B.a8l=new A.dt("Adding States","**Double-tap** on any empty area of the canvas to create a new state (circle).\n\nStates represent positions your machine can be in while reading input. You can drag states around to arrange your diagram.",B.a88)
B.a8c=new A.hz(2,"addTransition")
B.a8B=new A.dt("Drawing Transitions",'Hold **Shift** and drag from one state to another to draw a transition arrow.\n\nAfter drawing, **tap the label** on the arrow to set which input symbol it reads (e.g. "a", "b", "0", "1"). A single arrow can carry multiple symbols \u2014 separate them with commas.',B.a8c)
B.a8d=new A.hz(3,"setAccepting")
B.a8w=new A.dt("Accept States",'A state shown with a **double ring** is an accepting state \u2014 the machine accepts the input if it finishes in one of these.\n\nTo make a state accepting: **tap it** to open its menu, then toggle **"Accept"**.',B.a8d)
B.a8e=new A.hz(4,"setStartArrow")
B.a8k=new A.dt("The Start Arrow","Every automaton needs exactly **one start state** \u2014 the state it begins in.\n\nDrag the floating start arrow onto a state to set it as the start. If no start arrow is visible, use the **toolbar** to place one.",B.a8e)
B.a8j=new A.hz(9,"deleteMode")
B.a8C=new A.dt("Deleting Things","Made a mistake? Use the **trash-can** button in the toolbar to enter delete mode.\n\nIn delete mode, **tap** any state or transition arrow to remove it. Tap the trash-can again to exit delete mode.",B.a8j)
B.a89=new A.hz(10,"checkAnswer")
B.a8r=new A.dt("Checking Your Answer",'When you think your automaton is correct, tap **"Check"** in the top-right corner.\n\nThe app will test your machine against the target language. If they match, the level is complete! If not, you\'ll see a **counterexample** \u2014 a string your machine handles differently from the target.',B.a89)
B.Sa=s([B.a8m,B.a8l,B.a8B,B.a8w,B.a8k,B.a8C,B.a8r],t.nY)
